functions (like neural networks) can be treated as a Banach space, which is a type of mathematical space that is complete and equipped with a norm.</li><li><strong>Splines in Low Dimensions</strong>: In simpler settings, like low-dimensional spaces, splines (a type of function) are often used for approximation. They are chosen based on their smoothness, which can be quantified using norms.</li></ul></li><li><p><strong>Example - Multilayer Perceptrons</strong>:</p><ul><li><strong>Universal Approximators</strong>: Multilayer perceptrons, a basic type of feedforward neural network, are universal approximators. Even with just one hidden layer, they can represent a combination of step functions, allowing them to approximate any continuous function with arbitrary precision.</li></ul></li></ol><p>In summary, this section emphasizes that while neural networks have the capacity to approximate a wide variety of functions, the choice of the simplest and most regular function that fits the data (in terms of inductive bias) is crucial. This balance between flexibility and simplicity is key in designing effective machine learning models.</p></div></div></div><div class="mt-1 flex justify-start gap-3 empty:hidden"><div class="text-gray-400 flex self-end lg:self-center justify-center lg:justify-start mt-0 -ml-1 visible"><span class="" data-state="closed"><button class="flex items-center gap-1.5 rounded-md p-1 text-xs text-token-text-tertiary hover:text-token-text-primary md:invisible md:group-hover:visible md:group-[.final-completion]:visible"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="icon-md"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M12 4C10.8954 4 10 4.89543 10 6H14C14 4.89543 13.1046 4 12 4ZM8.53513 4C9.22675 2.8044 10.5194 2 12 2C13.4806 2 14.7733 2.8044 15.4649 4H17C18.6569 4 20 5.34315 20 7V19C20 20.6569 18.6569 22 17 22H7C5.34315 22 4 20.6569 4 19V7C4 5.34315 5.34315 4 7 4H8.53513ZM8 6H7C6.44772 6 6 6.44772 